Finally another place, in addition to the Comptoir by Chahinez, which is worth the detour.
Cozy, soft atmosphere, no loud music.

In short, to enjoy a moment of serenity and pleasure, don't hesitate to take a break

review_id:
Bonne experience dans l'ensemble, bel endroit, tres bon accueil, musique agreable, on est parti pour un brunch et le service etait rapide.
On a pris un brunch simple et un autre parisien, la charcuterie c'etait du pate mais bon, le fromage c'etait une portion vache qui rit, le beurre c'etait plutot de la margarine, le miel plutot 3sila et le jus d'orange industriel (excellence rouiba). Donc les produits pas authentiques mais au moins bons et de bonnes marques. Le croissant fourre, le the, le cafe au lait, le toasts, les pancakes et les oeufs etaient TOP.
Verdict : je recommande vu le manque de brunch en Algerie et reviendrai probablement.
review_text:
Bonne experience dans l'ensemble, bel endroit, tres bon accueil, musique agreable, on est parti pour un brunch et le service etait rapide.
On a pris un brunch simple et un autre parisien, la charcuterie c'etait du pate mais bon, le fromage c'etait une portion vache qui rit, le beurre c'etait plutot de la margarine, le miel plutot 3sila et le jus d'orange industriel (excellence rouiba). Donc les produits pas authentiques mais au moins bons et de bonnes marques. Le croissant fourre, le the, le cafe au lait, le toasts, les pancakes et les oeufs etaient TOP.
Verdict : je recommande vu le manque de brunch en Algerie et reviendrai probablement.
review_translated_text:
Good experience overall, nice place, very warm welcome, pleasant music, we went for brunch and the service was fast.
We had a simple brunch and another Parisian one, the charcuterie was pate but good, the cheese was a laughing cow portion, the butter was more like margarine, the honey more like 3sila and the juice industrial orange (rouiba excellence). So the products are not authentic but at least good and from good brands. The stuffed croissant, tea, coffee with milk, toast, pancakes and eggs were TOP.
Verdict: I recommend given the lack of brunch in Algeria and will probably come back.

Alors un mot allez y que ce soit en couples ou en famille,seul pour un moment de detente apres du shopping .

La responsable Madame waffa de cette brasserie au cadre idylique se fera un plaisir de vous acceuillir a bras ouverts.

review_translated_text:
You want to take a break from the day, so I advise you to stop there.
Whether salty or sweet, hot or cold, all your desires will be satisfied.
Served by a welcoming and helpful staff, you can enjoy dishes and pizzas with pies, all homemade and pleasantly surprised by the freshness of the products and the refinement of the dishes which will delight your taste buds.
So a word, go there whether as a couple or as a family, alone for a moment of relaxation after shopping.
The must have are the griouches which I completely fell in love with.
The manager Madame Waffa of this brasserie with its idyllic setting will be happy to welcome you with open arms.
It took me a while to find it but now it's one of my favorites for you who are in Oran welcome to La pausa.
